# Taxfyle Database Data Dictionary

## Overview

This document describes the structure and logic of the Taxfyle database for use in building the daily sales dashboard. The database contains job-level data that complements HubSpot data for comprehensive reporting.

---

## Database Connection (Metabase/BigQuery)

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Table** | `dbt_models.fct_jobs` |
| **Database** | BigQuery |
| **Timezone** | America/New_York (Miami) |

### BigQuery Date/Time Syntax

Always convert timestamps to Miami timezone for analysis:

```sql
-- Convert timestamp to Miami timezone
DATETIME(date_first_submitted, 'America/New_York')

-- Get current timestamp in Miami timezone
DATETIME(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), 'America/New_York')

-- Extract just the date
DATE(DATETIME(date_first_submitted, 'America/New_York'))

-- Extract hour (for hourly analysis)
EXTRACT(HOUR FROM DATETIME(date_first_submitted, 'America/New_York'))

-- Extract day of year (for YoY comparisons)
EXTRACT(DAYOFYEAR FROM DATETIME(date_first_submitted, 'America/New_York'))

-- Same day last year
DATE_SUB(DATE(DATETIME(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), 'America/New_York')), INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
```

