**Note**: If HubSpot deal data is already in BigQuery via these tables, you may NOT need a separate data pipeline. Check if `dim_deal_hubspot` has call activity and pipeline stage data.

### HubSpot Data (Call Center Metrics)

Call center performance data lives in **HubSpot Deals** (not Contacts):

| Data Point | Location | Notes |
|------------|----------|-------|
| Call attempts | Deal activity | Each call logged on the Deal |
| Call outcome (connected/voicemail/no answer) | Deal activity | Determines contact coverage |
| Deal stage changes | Deal properties | Pipeline progression |
| Quote presented timestamp | Deal properties | Starts 24-hour clock |
| Closed Won/Lost | Deal properties | Final outcome |

**Note**: Sales Factory has a separate deal pipeline per workspace (except Empower, which uses an internal pipeline). All POS workspaces: Taxfyle B2C, Rocket Lawyer, PRISM, Vensure, Pinnacle, Berkshire, Empower.

**Data Fragmentation**: BigQuery has job-level data; HubSpot has call center/deal data. A unified view requires either piping HubSpot data into BigQuery or building reports across both tools.

